Thread-Const - Constant strings efficiently shared between threads

This module generates constant values that can be shared among threads. This may reduce memory usage because the variable won't be copied.

INSTALLATION

To install this module, run the following commands:

	perl Build.PL
	./Build
	./Build test
	./Build install

SUPPORT AND DOCUMENTATION

After installing, you can find documentation for this module with the
perldoc command.

    perldoc Thread::Const

You can also look for information at:

    RT, CPAN's request tracker
        http://rt.cpan.org/NoAuth/Bugs.html?Dist=Thread-Const

    AnnoCPAN, Annotated CPAN documentation
        http://annocpan.org/dist/Thread-Const

    CPAN Ratings
        http://cpanratings.perl.org/d/Thread-Const

    Search CPAN
        http://search.cpan.org/dist/Thread-Const


